<p>Hello {!Opportunity.Account} Teachers and Staff!</p>

<p>We are Live Different, a trusted youth empowerment organization that has partnered with over 3,800 schools the past 19 years, and we'll be visiting yours on {!Opportunity.Invoice_Date__c}. We are very excited to provide your students with our 1-hour presentation called <strong>OWN YOUR STORY</strong>.</p>

<p><strong>2019/2020 Presentation Theme: OWN YOUR STORY</strong></p>

<p>This year's theme is all about helping to develop resilient, compassionate young people within our schools. With "Own Your Story", we hope to have students recognizing the beauty within their own story, understanding the agency they have in turning experience into growth, and finding meaning and purpose in helping others.</p>

<p><u>Classroom Activities</u></p>

<p>We are also providing a resource package attached to this email (including pre and post presentation activities) that you can use in your classroom to help continue important conversations and extend the impact of the presentation day events.
Thanks so much for your support and involvement in this initiative! These follow-up reflection opportunities are so important to our program having its greatest impact. We are confident that this year, working together, we can help your students understand just how important it is to "Own Your Story".</p>

<p><u>Connect with us!</u></p>

<p>I would love to hear back from you with any thoughts or <a href="https://www.tfaforms.com/forms/view/4705343?tfa_2={!Account.Name}&tfa_45={!Account.Id}&tfa_82={!Opportunity.Id}">feedback</a> about the presentation, these resources, and how they worked. My contact information is below, please reach out to me anytime! Additionally, if you are interested in learning more about Live Different or other programs such as our <a href="https://livedifferent.com/builds/" >Builds service learning trips</a>, I would be pleased to connect more about that as well!</p>

